{{Infobox Software | name = ACD/ChemSketch | logo = ChemSketchPlain.svg | latest release version = | latest release date = | operating system = [[Mac OS X]], [[Microsoft Windows]] | developer = [[Advanced_Chemistry_Development|ACD/Labs]] | language = | genre = Scientific | license = [[Proprietary software|Proprietary]] | website = [http://www.acdlabs.com/products/draw_nom/draw/chemsketch/ ChemSketch on ACD/Labs site (Commercial version)] [http://www.acdlabs.com/resources/freeware/chemsketch/ ChemSketch on ACD/Labs site (Freeware version)] }}
[[File:Aspirina animada.gif|thumb|Model of 2-Formyloxybenzoic acid, created using ACD/ChemSketch.]]
'''ACD/ChemSketch''' is a [[molecular modeling]] program used to create and modify images of [[chemical structure]]s. Also, there is a [[software]] that allows molecules and molecular models displayed in two and three dimensions, to understand the structure of chemical bonds and the nature of the [[functional groups]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Chemsketch|url=http://escritoriodocentes.educ.ar/datos/cie_acd_chemsketch_free.html|accessdate=21 August 2014}}</ref>
== Features == {{expand section|date=October 2015}} The program offers some advanced features that allows the [[molecule]]s rotate and apply color to improve visualization. It has several templates with ions and functional groups with the possibility to add text and use other tools to optimize productions created by the software.<ref name="Eduteka Chemsketch">{{cite web|title=Utilizando Chemsketch|url=http://www.eduteka.org/ChemSketch.php|accessdate=21 August 2014}}</ref>
== Applications == Using ACD/ChemSketch is primarily for educational use. With this program it is possible to write and perform [[chemical equations]], diagrams laboratories and [[chemical structure]]s of various entity.<ref name="Eduteka Chemsketch"/>
