The ministry for '''Sport, Arts and Recreation''' is a department in the Zimbabwean government which is responsible for the operation of sports and development of the arts within the country. The position was created by President [[Emmerson Mnangagwa]] following his cabinet formation in December 2017 when he split [[Ministry_of_Higher_Education, Science_and_Technology_(Zimbabwe)|Higher Education]] and [[Ministry_of_Primary_and_Secondary_Education_(Zimbabwe)|Primary and Secondary Eucation]] into two separate government agencies, the latter being responsible for sports and the arts prior to this move. 

The minister is former Olympic swimmer and record holder [[Kirsty Coventry]].

