* {{cite journal |last1=Smithells |first1=R. W. |title=The Liverpool Congenital Abnormalities Registry |journal=Developmental Medicine & Child Neurology |date=June 1962 |volume=4 |issue=3 |pages=320–324 |doi=10.1111/j.1469-8749.1962.tb03174.x }}
* {{cite journal |last1=Smithells |first1=R. W. |title=RUBELLA IN PREGNANCY |journal=Developmental Medicine & Child Neurology |date=December 1962 |volume=46 |issue=6 |pages=640–642 |doi=10.1111/j.1469-8749.1962.tb04158.x }}
Smithells wrote the following books that described diagnostic methods before the rise of [[ultrasound]] scans.<ref>{{cite web |title=Vignette: paediatrician and researcher Richard Worthington Smithells |url=https://www.mddus.com/resources/publications-library/insight/summer-2013/vignette-richard-w-smithells |website=MDDUS |publisher=The Medical and Dental Defence Union of Scotland |accessdate=10 July 2018}}</ref>
* The Early Diagnosis of Congenital Abnormalities., R W Smithells. Cassell: London, 1963. * Why are babies born deformed? R W Smithells. [[University of Exeter]], 1983. * Clinical examination of children., S R Meadow; R W Smithells. Blackwell Scientific Publications, 1991
==Awards and honours== In 1985, Smithells was awarded the [[Harding award]] in 1985 from [[Action Medical Research|Action Research for the Crippled Child]]<ref name="munk"/> In 1992, Smithells was awarded the prestigious [[James Spence Medal|James Spence Gold Medal]] in 1992, by the [[Royal College of Paediatrics and Child Health]].<ref name="rcp"/> The [[Rank Prize for Nutrition]] followed and was awarded jointly in 1995.<ref name="welcome"/> In 1998 he won the [[Dawson Williams Memorial Prize]] of the [[British Medical Association]].<ref name="welcome"/> During 2000, Smithells won the International Research Award of the [[Joseph P. Kennedy Jr. Foundation|Joseph P Kennedy Foundation]] for research into the role of [[folic acid]] in preventing neural tube defects.<ref name="leeds"/>
